<br>
But really, what can you expect when you've kicked the biggest bully in the nuts.<br>
<br>
Ok, maybe you only let this guy live in your country, and your not behind what he did, or help do. This may sound cruel, but Im sorry, we must inflict a large enough wound, so that no country will harbour such an ass bite anymore.<br>
<br>
We've been put in a corner, please dont be offended if we come out swinging. <br>
<br>
And NO way would it take us YEARS to wipe out any oppositioon in the middle east. Please dont prey on our our cowards with such propiganda.<br>
<br>
<br>
My best advice to the author: become an American. after all, all of us came here from another country, because we wanted to. If you dont bleed red, white and blue.. maybe you dont belong here after all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uealan01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ealan01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/18/01 10:29:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Words of an Afghani living in the US</span><hr size=1> Actually, I would say that opposition in the Middle East (Afghanistan is not part of the Middle East, btw) can *never* be &quot;wiped out&quot;.<br>
<br>
What we *can* do is swing public opinion of the islamic nations over to our side so *they* take an active role in removing terrorist elements internally.<br>
<br>
You've got to understand that these elements represent a very dangerous minority in most of these countries and that taking them on could result in the country falling apart.  It must be approached with caution and intelligence.<br>
<br>
Bombing a nation with tens of millions of people in order to cripple a military regime of less than 100,000 isn't going to accomplish that...<br>
