<br>
We may need to help moderate the Kashmir dispute.<br>
<br>
We may also need to take a more active role in resolving the Palestinian crisis.<br>
<br>
We may need (and this is the big one, really) to pledge military support to governments who are trying to extricate this terrorist element from their country.<br>
<br>
To be honest, that's what I think these nations are looking for and that is what I assume we are providing.  That is why the conflict will be &quot;long and drawn out&quot; and will be a &quot;new kind of war&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulargar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Largar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/18/01 11:02:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Words of an Afghani living in the US</span><hr size=1> [qoute]We may also need to take a more active role in resolving the Palestinian crisis. [/qoute]<br>
