<br>
I think it is important that we not abandon Israel (our ally), but I also think that it may be time for us to take a hard look at both sides of the issue and try to find some mutually acceptable solution.  Palestinians have been suicide bombing Israel for years and Israel has returned the favor with military action.<br>
<br>
The cycle of death there fuels the other islamic nations (who don't need a lot of convincing to hate Israel) and makes the terrorists look like heroes (to the impressionable).<br>
<br>
The whole world has sort of ignored the issue (for the most part) while it has gotten worse.  It's the old &quot;ah, those people have been killing each other forever&quot; argument.  I don't for a minute think that the Palestinian situation is the sole cause of what happened Tuesday (Bin Laden has his own lunatic agenda), but rather I think that helping to resolve it would win a lot of favor among normal muslims. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#E9D756>- </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr>Erollisi Marr, The Queen of Love</a><font color=#E9D756> - </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18>America Under Attack</a> <font color=#E9D756> - </font> <br>
